                  <persName id="t18260112-34-person299">
                  CHARLES 
                  WARD
               <interp inst="t18260112-34-person299" type="surname" value="WARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260112-34-person299" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260112-34-person299" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am in the employ of Hannah Winter, a <rs id="t18260112-34-viclabel202" type="occupation">widow</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260112-34-victim298 t18260112-34-viclabel202"></join>, who is a <rs id="t18260112-34-viclabel203" type="occupation">coppersmith</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260112-34-victim298 t18260112-34-viclabel203"></join>, and lives in <placeName id="t18260112-34-crimeloc204">Houndsditch</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18260112-34-crimeloc204" type="placeName" value="Houndsditch"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18260112-34-crimeloc204" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260112-34-off200 t18260112-34-crimeloc204"></join>. The prisoner was in her employ. On the 14th of December, between four and five o'clock, I received information from a lad, and found 13lbs. or 14lbs. of solder concealed in a copper, in front of the shop. I marked it, and watched to see who would come for it; the prisoner left off work at six o'clock; I wanted him to stop till ten, which he objected to; I went to the copper at six, and the solder was gone. I followed the prisoner, and took him eight or nine doors off, and found it concealed in the waist-hand of his trousers - he said he was not the only one.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ALLEY. Q. He was extremely sorry? A. Yes; he has lived nearly twenty years with my mistress.</p>

               <p>The prisoner received an excellent character.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18260112-34-verdict205" type="verdictDescription">
